led *guides* if no one is going to listen to them and pull stuff anyway, I could of been off getting exp and much better loot a lot of higher lvl zones but I CHOSE to be at the raids to help.......and not that it means a whole lot either but you know not ONE single person ever said so much as thx for pulling or thx for helping.  <p>Demun Soulslayer<br>51 Champion<br>Its all fun and games<br> until someone gets knocked down,<br>knocked up,<br>or knocked the F#@k out.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/udemunsoulslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Demun Soulslayer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bloodcircle.com/bcicon3.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/1/01 1:14:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1E1E1E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/usilvethon23.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvethon23</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/01 1:55:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tonight's raid</span><hr size=1> <br>
Ok, Demun, I will take this oppertunity now to say thanks. Perhaps it is a bit late, but I truly do appreciate you helping out. You did a great job pulling and were everyone else there of the same mindset of you, I doubt it would have been so confused.<br>
<br>
Like I said, I am not accusing anyone and I am kind of seeing that higher levels can get swept away in the chaos of one of these midlevel raids just as easily as the midlevels. There is no need to be defensive.<br>
<br>
However, I would like to point out that it was not the &quot;lower and mid lvl's [that] just didnt seem to want to sit still&quot; Most of the extra pulls were brought by a couple of higher levels that were impatient with the speed at which we were getting keys and getting through the floors. Specifically, I remember a 50+ bard (name escapes me) who was a very nice person but didn't seem awfully interested in midlevels getting xp. <br>
<br>
Now, let me clarify the whole key farming thing and &quot;coming for their own purposes&quot; thing... I was not trying to imply that anyone was using the raid as a tool for getting loot or for getting keys that they would use as a later date. What I was saying was that on the lower floors, the raid mentality seemed to be to get keys as fast as possible and move up to higher level floors (ultimately Tserrina) without thought to xp for the midlevels. What I had in mind when we started was to milk each floor all possible xp before moving up then milking the next floor; I think it is obvious that the raid wasn't approached in this manner.  I am not trying to say that anyone came out of greed or anything like that, only that the goals of many there were different than the original goals of the raid. <br>
<br>
In response to the raiders listening to my so-called &quot;guides&quot;, I realize that this is ALWAYS a problem on most raids. People listening to those in charge is an obviously integral part of any raid situation. Not so obvious, however, is how the leaders (guides) are themselves implemented. I thought that this perhaps needed some light shed on it and is why I chose to look at the other night from this angle instead of a more traditional listen-to-the-leaders type of thing. <br>
<br>
I understand that this may sound selfish, but it really was set up FOR the mid-levels so I think they have a right to be a bit selfish. <br>
<br>
Thanks again Demun, I would reiterate that I mean no offense to anyone personally. <br>
<br>
