 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uthemaunster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>the Maunster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/01 2:51:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tonight's raid</span><hr size=1> Like I said before, Demun, I appreciate your pullng a lot, and also as I said, I am glad that all of the higher levels showed up for the support.  I think however, that part of the reason others started pulling at MM was that they were bored.  I for one hit each mob once, if that, and then it was dead.  coulda been a combination of having a lot of people there and having high level folks there, but also as I said before, these mobs could have been pulled by someone of a lower level, or even after having been pulled, been taunted off by those who were there for the MID LEVEL RAID.  We had a guy in our group who went in the other room and fought by himself, because he wasn't getting any nukes in.  And my point in even saying anything is, What's the fun in sitting there doing nothing or as Silvethon put it, tagging along?<br>
<br>
I guess it's pointless to re-hash, because it is over, and I don't even expect an apology, because I'm sure there will be a reason or excuse for anything I might bring up.  But for the next time we have a mid-level raid... please, try to keep in mind that we mid-level folk are there to have fun, kick some butt, and if possible pick up some exp or loot along the way.. all the same reasons you'd go on any raid.  If the high-level people do it all, what's left for us?<br>
